3. Visual Identity System
Logo Evolution
Current state: A watch emoji (⌚) + "MicrobrandHub" in a sans-serif wordmark. Functional but emoji-dependent and visually generic at small sizes.

Evolution direction — "The Meridian Mark":

Keep the watch as the core iconographic element but evolve it into a bespoke icon:

Icon: A minimal watch face rendered as a precise circle with a single applied hour marker at 12 o'clock and slim, sword-style hands pointing to 10:10. No case lugs shown — pure dial face. The circle has a hairline double-ring border (outer thick, inner thin) referencing both watch chapter rings and precision drafting.
Wordmark: Set in a refined geometric grotesque — optically spaced, slightly tracked out, with "Microbrand" in medium weight and "Hub" in light weight — creating hierarchy within the wordmark itself.
Relationship: Icon sits left, wordmark right, aligned on centerline. Minimum clear space: half the icon height on all sides.
Icon-only version: The dial face alone, used at favicon scale and app icon contexts. Works in single color.
Reversed version: White on deep navy or charcoal for dark mode and photography overlays.
What to avoid: Any further use of the watch emoji character — it renders inconsistently across platforms and signals "early-stage project" rather than "established authority."

