Usage Rules
Lume Green (#B8FF6E) is the single electric accent — used only on primary CTAs, active states, and key numerical callouts. Never use as a background color across large areas. Its power comes from restraint.
Copper Pusher (#C4793A) provides editorial warmth — use for pull quotes, category labels, and review scores. Never pair directly with Lume Green.
Dark mode is primary — the site currently runs dark and should lean into it fully. Light mode is available for print/editorial contexts.
Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for all body text (WCAG AA). Lume Green on Midnight Dial passes at 8.2:1.
