Implementation Priorities — Quick Wins First
For maximum impact with minimum rebuild time, recommend this phased rollout:

Phase 1 — Identity (Weeks 1–2): Update tagline, swap emoji for custom logo mark, apply color tokens, load Syne + JetBrains Mono fonts. Cost: low. Impact: immediate.

Phase 2 — Homepage (Weeks 2–4): Rebuild hero section, add stats ticker, add "0 paid inclusions" trust badge, upgrade CTA button styles. Cost: medium. Impact: high on first impressions.

Phase 3 — Brand Cards & Directory (Weeks 4–8): Redesign brand card components, add filter system, upgrade review card layout. Cost: medium-high. Impact: high on core utility.

Phase 4 — Editorial (Weeks 8–12): Review page rebuild, score system, editorial pull quotes, author profiles. Cost: medium. Impact: high on time-on-site and trust.

Phase 5 — Community & Newsletter (Weeks 12+): Newsletter template rebuild, social content system, community features. Cost: ongoing. Impact: long-term compounding.

